      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Cytokines are the chemical messengers of this immune \"battle,\" acting as the signaling system to call in reinforcements. During an intense acute infection, inflammatory cytokines like **IL-1** and **TNF-$\\alpha$** are released, which dramatically increase vascular permeability and induce adhesion molecules on endothelial cells, allowing neutrophils to squeeze out of the blood vessels. Meanwhile, interleukins like **IL-2** are crucial for T-lymphocyte proliferation and activation, guiding the adaptive response within the lymphoid tissues.",
